Aug 23 2007 	Great location	I have stayed at the Piccolino twice now and found it was comfortable both times. The staff are very pleasant, and the location - just down the road from Paddington station - is excellent. The Bakerloo line from Paddington is great for getting around the city. Hyde park is just down the road, and there is a very nice pub, the Queen Victoria, just a few doors down for the hotel. The rooms very basic but comfortable. On my first stay, in 2005, the room was lovely, but without a view. On the second, in 2006, we were rather disturbed by the boiler in the attic, but the room itself was comfortable.The breakfast is good, with lots of coffee or tea, cereal and mini pastries and fruit, of which you can eat all you like. There is also toast. I liked this hotel, it is a quiet, pleasant base for a visit to the capital and I would recommend it to others for the brilliant location.	
