Apr 23 2007	Pleasant good location	Pleasant small hotel in the hotel-dense area near Paddington, along and just off Sussex Gardens. This one is just five minutes from Paddington, straight up the street, and not much longer the other way to Hyde Park, ideal when the sun is shining. I asked for and got a quiet room at the back. Very pleasant reception person. While the en suite toilet, sink, shower is a triumph of design over physical space, it was nicely tiled with modern fittings and plenty of hot water in the well working shower. The beds were fine and the TV included a wide range of Sky channels.The breakfast is advertised as &quot;continental&quot;, but no one on the continent would put up with a rather mediocre selection of a few cereals and white bread toast. Given the modest price, for London, of a stay here, anyone liking a good breakfast should walk up the road to Paddington Station, there are at least two places open and advertising full breakfast for less than five pounds, and the station concourse has a range of chain food outlets.	
