Dec 11 2006 	Not bad for a budget London hotel	This is a reasonable quality budget hotel in a busy part of London. Don't expect the Ritz, but good enough and certainly a million times better than many London hotels I have stayed in. I ended up here after the neighbouring hotel let me down on a booking. The staff in the Piccolino were extremely friendly and did me a special deal on a triple room (even though there was only one of me!). The room was clean, pleasant and large. There was a Sky box (unusually) allowing a broader range of satellite channels than usual.Only negatives (which is why it gets three stars):- It is on a very busy road and the windows are only single-glazed, therefore noisy if your room faces the street, with taxis whizzing past and people talking- The breakfast is basic - coffee/tea, toast, cereals and a small bowl of fruit. No cooked breakfastsHaving said all that it only cost me £70 for the night, which for the money is excellent in London and if I wanted a cheap hotel in a good location I would stay there again.	
